# Always commit and push

When you finish implementation changes in this repository:

1. **Commit** relevant changes without waiting to be asked.
2. **Push** to `origin` so Lovable can sync and Publish picks up updates.
3. Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials, API keys).
4. Stage only files related to the task; skip unrelated generated churn unless it was part of the work.
5. Use clear commit messages focused on why the change was made.

If push fails, report what was committed locally and the error.
